FBIS3-12632 "drnes042_k_94002" FBIS-NES-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 IRAQ U.S. Mine Explodes, Kills 3 Children in Safwan JN0303104394 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0940 GMT 3 Mar 94 JN0303104394 Baghdad INA Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Al-Basrah, southern Iraq, 3 Mar (INA)--Three children have been killed in the Safwan subdistrict when a mine dropped on farms there by U.S. aircraft during the hateful 30-state aggression went off. The newspaper AL-THAWRAH, quoting its correspondent in al-Basrah, said that when it went off, the mine killed two children instantly, tearing their bodies apart. As for the third child, he first lost his four limbs. He later died on his way to hospital. The paper indicated that this incident is the third in the past two weeks. All in all, these incidents have killed six children and wounded 10 others in Safwan and nearby farms.
